{
  "_doc": [
    "Manual venue overrides applied during ingestion and after geocoding.",
    "",
    "SECTIONS",
    "\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550",
    "canonical_names \u2014 Venue deduplication (same ground, different name strings).",
    "  Each entry defines one physical venue:",
    "    canonical  : the single name to store in the DB",
    "    city       : optional; used in country resolution and DB insert",
    "    country    : optional; if set, overrides geocoding for these names",
    "    aliases    : every name variant that should map to this venue",
    "  During ingestion any alias is silently rewritten to the canonical name before",
    "  the DB lookup, so no duplicate rows are created.",
    "  Run `python -m db.dedup_venues` (then --commit) to merge existing duplicates.",
    "",
    "  Workflow to add a new canonical group:",
    "    SELECT venue_id, name, city, COUNT(*) FROM history.matches m",
    "    JOIN history.venues v USING (venue_id)",
    "    WHERE name ILIKE '%keyword%' GROUP BY 1,2,3 ORDER BY 4 DESC;",
    "  Pick the name with the most matches as canonical (or the current official name).",
    "",
    "Country override tiers \u2014 most specific wins:",
    "  1. canonical_names[].country \u2014 if set, applied to the canonical name",
    "  2. by_name_city  \u2014 exact case-insensitive name, optional city",
    "  3. by_name_pattern \u2014 city + name substring",
    "  4. by_city       \u2014 exact city match",
    "",
    "After resolving to a raw country, west_indies_countries remaps all WI member",
    "nations to the canonical 'West Indies' string.",
    "",
    "Last updated: 2026-06-04"
  ],
